Four Japanese held in China for
allegedly videotaping military targets are employees of Fujita
Corp., Kyodo News reported, citing Japanâ€™s foreign ministry.  The employees visited Hebei, China on company business
unrelated to military issues, Yoshiaki Onodera, a spokesman for
the Japanese company, said today by phone in response to an
earlier Xinhua news agency report.  Fujita, a Tokyo-based general contractor acquired by
